Date: October 25, 2025
Issue: Hero text not showing, CSS class name visible, background too large
Status: ✅ FIXED



❌ .hero-video-bg CSS class name showing as text on page
❌ Hero title and subtitle not visible
❌ Background image/video too large and overflowing
❌ Layout positioning issues





Quarto div syntax issue - Using ::: {.hero-video-bg} wasn’t rendering correctly
Z-index layering - Hero content was behind the video/overlay
Flexbox layout - display: flex on hero-section was causing positioning issues
Background attachment - Fixed background was causing sizing problems






Before:
::: {.hero-video-bg}
&lt;video ...&gt;
:::
After:
&lt;div class="hero-video-bg"&gt;
  &lt;video ...&gt;
  &lt;/video&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
Changed from Quarto div syntax to proper HTML &lt;div&gt; tags because Quarto wasn’t processing the video element correctly inside the div syntax.



Z-index hierarchy: - Video container: z-index: 0 - Video overlay: z-index: 1 - Hero content: z-index: 10
Key changes: - Removed display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center from .hero-section - Changed video container from z-index: -1 to z-index: 0 - Increased hero content z-index to 10 (was 2) - Added pointer-events: none to video container - Added position: relative; z-index: 10 to hero title and subtitle



Changes: - Removed background-attachment: fixed (causes sizing issues) - Added max-width: none to video element - Set explicit padding: 80px 32px instead of CSS variables - Changed min-height from 500px to 600px



Changed subtitle color: - Before: color: var(--bim-light-gray) (hard to read) - After: color: var(--bim-white) (crisp and readable)



Added specific mobile styles:
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero-section {
    min-height: 400px;
    padding: 48px 16px;
  }

  .hero-title, .hero-title h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
  }

  .hero-subtitle, .hero-subtitle p {
    font-size: 18px;
  }
}




