Date: October 25, 2025
Issue: Orange boxes covering content in “Specialized Industry Expertise” section
Status: ✅ FIXED


The CTA buttons (.cta-primary) inside feature cards were appearing as large orange boxes that covered the card content. The text content was only visible on hover, which was not the intended behavior.



The feature cards lacked proper layout structure, causing the CTA buttons to: 1. Expand to fill available space 2. Potentially overlap or obscure text content above them 3. Display incorrectly without proper alignment



Added flexbox layout to .feature-card and specific styling for .cta-primary buttons within cards:


.feature-card {
  background: white;
  padding: 32px;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--bim-orange);
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  display: flex;              /* NEW */
  flex-direction: column;     /* NEW */
}

/* CTA buttons inside feature cards - NEW SECTION */
.feature-card .cta-primary {
  margin-top: auto;           /* Pushes button to bottom */
  margin-bottom: 0;
  align-self: flex-start;     /* Aligns to left, not stretch */
  width: auto;                /* Prevents full-width expansion */
  display: inline-block;
}

.feature-card .cta-primary:hover {
  text-decoration: none;      /* Removes underline on hover */
}





Flexbox Layout: display: flex; flex-direction: column; creates a vertical stack within the card
Button Positioning: margin-top: auto pushes the button to the bottom of the card
Button Size: width: auto; display: inline-block; ensures button only takes up needed space
Alignment: align-self: flex-start keeps button left-aligned instead of stretching full-width




After this fix: - ✅ Text content (title, experience, specialization) is always visible - ✅ CTA button appears as a normal-sized orange button at the bottom - ✅ Button text is readable (“Explore Warehouse Solutions →”, etc.) - ✅ Button hovers correctly with color change - ✅ No content is hidden or obscured



